based on the CS:APP Malloc Lab (c) by R.Bryant and D.O'Hallaron.

0. Files:
---------

all file based on segregated free list structure.

mm.c, mm_Size_based_split_96.c : Size based split using k = 96
mm_Size_based_split_128.c : Size based split using k = 128
mm_Ordinary_split.c : Ordinary split


if you want test other code, change mm.c file

ex) you want get ordinary split results, then remove mm.c file, and rename mm_Ordinary_split.c to mm.c file.


1. Building and running the driver
----------------------------------

To build the driver, type "make" to the shell.

To run the driver on a tiny test trace:

  $ mdriver -V -f short1-bal.rep

The -V option prints out helpful tracing and summary information.

To get a list of the driver flags:

  $ mdriver -h

To test all of trace, (to get paper result)

  $ mdriver -v
